  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This is an observational study looking at the characteristics of patients consulting for
      genital warts in the first semester 2010 at the public sexual health clinic of Valparaiso,
      Chile. The objectives are: to have an epidemiological profile, estimating cost of the disease
      for the health system and the patient and analyzing possible psychosocial consequences of the
      condition for the patients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
